          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The typical 32S beam current range was 70-90pnA",
                "monitored by a shielded suppressed Faraday cup at the",
                "periphery of the chamber. The beam energy loss in",
                "traveling half the target was calculated and was",
                "about 0.5 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "184W target with thickness about 200 ug/cm2 was",
                "evaporated on a 20 ug/cm2 thick carbon foil backing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Array of five Si detectors with a depletion",
                "depth ranging from 200 to 300 um covered the angular",
                "range of 14-35 degree, 35-55 degree and 55-75 degree",
                "was mounted on the movable arm in the vacuum chamber.",
                "Five masks were placed in the front of each detector",
                "to assure the angular resolution. The detector to the",
                "target distance was 27 cm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two groups of Si strip detectors were mounted",
                "on opposite sides of the beam. These Si strip",
                "detectors were 48 x 50 mm2 in area and each detector",
                "consisted of 24 strips. Due to a lack of readout",
                "electronics, the strips were tied together in groups",
                "of eight. Data from these strip detectors were",
                "recorded in the coincidence mode (Si strip and Si",
                "detectors) with the requirement that each detector",
                "was struck by a fission fragment."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Rutherford scattering was monitored at",
                "laboratory forward angle of 15 degree by four Si(Au)",
                "surface barrier detectors for the normalization of",
                "the cross-section measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between Si strip and Si detectors",
                "was required."
              ]
            }
          ],
